# Mikasa Dendry cheat sheet

Dendry (`.dry`) is compiled by [dendrynexus](https://github.com/aucchen/dendrynexus) into `out/`. Syntax below is inferred from this repo; confirm edge cases with `npm run dendrynexus make-html -- --pretty`.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `source/scenes/**/*.scene.dry` | Scenes, cards, events, advisors — **authoritative game logic** |
| `source/qdisplays/*.qdisplay.dry` | Qualities: numeric ranges → labels |
| `source/info.dry` | Game title / author metadata |
| `source/lib/*.js` | Dev/CLI mirrors only — not compiled into the playable build |
| `out/` | Generated HTML/JS — do not edit |

## Electorate modifier catalog

Story choices bump **stack** qualities on `on-arrival:` (e.g. `dundalk_reform += 1`). Poll effects come from rows in `Q.electorateModifierCatalog` in **`electorate_runtime.scene.dry`** (`MIKASA_ELECTORATE_RUNTIME_*` block). When you add a new stack in an event, add a matching `new ElectorateModifier(...)` row by hand (party, delta, scope, target).

## Scene file anatomy

```dry
title: My Scene
new-page: true
is-card: true
card-image: img/foo.jpg
tags: event, govt_affairs
priority: 1
max-visits: 1
view-if: month = 3 and year = 2300
on-arrival: foo += 1; bar = 1
go-to: post_event if started = 1; main if started = 0

Prose and choices here.

- @choice_a: Label shown to player
- @choice_b
- #event

@choice_a
title: Choice title (cards)
subtitle: Shown under title
choose-if: police_defund = 0 and police_reform < 2
available-if: police_investigated = 0
unavailable-subtitle: Why this is greyed out
on-arrival: police_reform += 1
on-depart: defund = 0

Choice body text.
[? if police_reform = 1: Conditional prose ?]
```

- **`@subscene`** — block starting with `@name`; choices use `- @name` or `- @name: visible label`.
- **`#tag`** — include all scenes tagged with that name (e.g. `- #event`, `- #party_affairs` in decks).
- **`=` heading** — section title in UI (`= Status`).
- **`>` blockquote** — quoted flavor text in `root.scene.dry`.

## Common scene metadata

| Key | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `title:` | Display name |
| `new-page:` | Open as new page (`true` / `false`) |
| `is-card:` | Playable card |
| `is-pinned-card:` | Stays in hand (e.g. advance month, advisors) |
| `is-hand:` / `is-deck:` | Main UI: hand vs deck |
| `max-cards:` | Hand size |
| `card-image:` | Card art path |
| `set-bg:` | Background image |
| `tags:` | Grouping for `#tag` includes and filters |
| `priority:` | Event ordering (higher first) |
| `max-visits:` | `1` = one-shot event/card setup |
| `view-if:` / `view_if:` | When scene/card appears (both spellings exist in repo) |
| `on-arrival:` | Run on enter — JS block `{! … !}` or `stat += 1; stat2 = 0` |
| `on-depart:` | Run when leaving subscene |
| `on-display:` | JS when scene renders (DOM / `fetch`, see `mod_loader.scene.dry`) |
| `go-to:` | Auto-navigate: `scene`, `scene.subscene`, or conditions |

### `go-to` examples (from repo)

```dry
go-to: post_event.events_choice
go-to: main
go-to: organize_phase_tick.scene.dry
go-to: events_choice if has_event = 1; main if has_event = 0
```

### Choice gating (subscenes)

| Key | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `choose-if:` / `chose-if:` | Must be true to pick (typo `chose-if` appears in source). No trailing `;`. Use `=` not `=>`. |
| `available-if:` | Alternative gating style (same condition rules) |
| `view-if:` / `view_if:` | When scene/card appears (same condition rules) |
| `unavailable-subtitle:` | Text when disabled; may embed `[? … ?]` |

Run `npm run lint:dendry` before committing scene changes.

## Inline templating

| Syntax | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `[+ var +]` | Insert quality/stat value |
| `[+ month : month +]` | Value with qdisplay label (see `month.qdisplay.dry`) |
| `[? if x = 1: text ?]` | Conditional prose (`=` only; `=>` is invalid in .dry conditions) |
| `{! JavaScript or HTML !}` | Execute JS or emit raw HTML |

HTML tooltips and party colors are common:

```dry
{!<span style="color: #44b88f;">C</span>!}:[+ Exec_C +]
```

Party letter colors: **C** corp `#44b88f`, **G** gang `#cf6e19`, **D** dem `#1100cc`, **H** hate `#3a0000ff`, **I** ind `#404040`.

## JavaScript blocks

- Wrap logic in `{! … !}` (multiline OK).
- **`Q`** — primary game state namespace (`Q.month`, `Q.update_projections()`, etc.). Runtime APIs are defined in silent setup scenes (`election_runtime`, `electorate_runtime`, `economic_assets_runtime`, `organize_phase_tick`, …), not in `source/lib/*.js`.
- Top-level assignments in `on-arrival` often omit `let`/`const` (Dendrynexus global scope).
- **`on-arrival:` without braces** — semicolon-separated stat updates: `on-arrival: patriot_meme_strength += 1;`
- Runtime APIs appear in advanced scenes: `this.game.scenes`, `this._compileChoices`, `this.ui` (`post_event.scene.dry`).

### Setup / tick pattern

Hidden setup scenes (`max-visits: 1`, `new-page: false`) define functions and assign hooks:

```dry
on-arrival: {!
function organize_tick() { Q.protest_good += Q.non_violence - 1.5 }
Q.monthly_tick_phase1 = monthly_tick_phase1
!}
```

Wire with `go-to:` from a visible card or `on-arrival` on phase start.

## Q-displays (`*.qdisplay.dry`)

Map numeric qualities to text:

```dry
(1..1) January
(0.41..0.54) divided
(..0.06) completely disloyal
(0.95..) completely loyal
```

Used via `[+ month : month +]` — second name is the qdisplay id (usually filename stem).

## Game flow (this project)

1. **`root.scene.dry`** — start menu, new-game stat init, build stamp. Bootstraps runtime scenes.
2. **`election_runtime.scene.dry`** — **source of truth** for election v2 (voter blocks, IGs, `DISTRICT_POPULATIONS`, tabulation). `source/lib/election-v2.js` is for Node CLI only.
3. **`electorate_runtime.scene.dry`** — `ElectorateModifier` catalog and `Q.applyElectorateModifiers`.
4. **`economic_assets_runtime.scene.dry`** — homes/assets API, Jacobs report helpers (not `source/lib/economic-asset-name-catalog.js`).
5. **`main.scene.dry`** — decks: Party Affairs, Government Affairs, pinned shuffle/advance.
6. **`advance.scene.dry`** — month tick → `post_event`.
7. **`post_event.scene.dry`** — month-end tick (`update_projections`, scheduled elections, event queue) or return to main.
8. **Events** — `tags: event`, `view-if:` date, `priority`, `max-visits: 1`.
9. **Cards** — `is-card: true`, `tags: organize_phase` / `govt_affairs` / `party_affairs`, often `view_if:` unlock flags.
10. **`status.scene.dry`**, **`library.scene.dry`**, **`election_simulation.scene.dry`** — `is-special: true`.
11. **`@backSpecialScene`** — return from special scenes (library, mods).

## Build

```bash
npm install
npm run make-html
cp source/robots.txt out/html/robots.txt   # crawler / AI-training opt-out (see file comments)
```

`make-html` embeds the compile in `out/html/core.js` via dendrynexus; no extra copy steps.

## Editing tips

- Prefer matching existing spelling in the same file (`view-if` vs `view_if`, `choose-if` vs `chose-if`).
- New events: copy a dated event (e.g. `september_convention.scene.dry`), set `view-if`, `tags: event`, add to event pool via `#event` if needed.
- New qualities: add qdisplay file + reference in prose with `[+ name : qdisplay_id +]`.
- Simulation / balance logic: edit runtime scenes (`election_runtime`, `electorate_runtime`, `economic_assets_runtime`, `organize_phase_tick`). CLI: `npm run simulate-election:v2 -- --from-scene` (extracts `MIKASA_*_BEGIN`/`END` from `.dry`, not from editing `source/lib/*.js`).
